getOrientation

public Matrix3f getOrientation(float time,
                               float precision)
getOrientation calculates the rotation matrix for any given point along to the line to still be facing in the direction of the line.

Parameters:
time - the current time (between 0 and 1)
precision - how accurate to (i.e. the next time) to check against.
Returns:
the rotation matrix.

com.jme.curve.Curve#getOrientation(float, float)

getOrientation

public Matrix3f getOrientation(float time,
                               float precision,
                               Vector3f up)
getOrientation calculates the rotation matrix for any given point along to the line to still be facing in the direction of the line. A up vector is supplied, this keep the rotation matrix following the line, but insures the object's up vector is not drastically changed.

Parameters:
time - the current time (between 0 and 1)
precision - how accurate to (i.e. the next time) to check against.
Returns:
the rotation matrix.
See Also:
com.jme.curve.Curve#getOrientation(float, float)

getPoint

public Vector3f getPoint(float time)

getPoint

public Vector3f getPoint(float time,
                         Vector3f point)
getPoint calculates a point on a Catmull-Rom curve from a given time value within the interval [0, 1]. If the value is zero or less, the first control point is returned. If the value is one or more, the last control point is returned. Using the equation of a Catmull-Rom Curve, the point at the interval is calculated and returned.

See Also:
com.jme.curve.Curve#getPoint(float)
